# Architecture Rules

## Rust layer
- instrument-core must NEVER import tauri, wasm-bindgen, tokio, or std::fs
- All Rust logic in instrument-core must be pure functions — no side effects
- Use thiserror for error types — never panic! in library code
- All public structs: #[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)] + #[serde(rename_all = "camelCase")]

## React / TypeScript layer
- All React components call src/bridge/index.ts only — never invoke() directly
- Platform detection uses isDesktop / isWeb from src/bridge/index.ts — never check __TAURI_INTERNALS__ in components
- Tool components are always lazy-loaded via React.lazy()
- src/constants/library.ts is the source of truth for category/role mappings

## Registry
- Every new tool must have an entry in src/registry/index.ts
- Registry drives Library display, search, routing, platform filtering, and history recording
- platforms: ["desktop", "web"] for cross-platform tools; platforms: ["desktop"] for native-only tools
- sensitive: true for any tool handling secrets, tokens, or keys (auto-skips history)

## WASM sync (critical)
- After any src-core/ Rust change: run `pnpm run build:wasm` and commit public/wasm-pkg/
- See wasm-workflow.mdc for the full workflow

## Package management
- Use pnpm for all package operations — never npm or yarn
- pnpm add for dependencies, pnpm add -D for dev, pnpm dlx for one-off CLIs

## General
- Inline comments explain WHY not WHAT
- Every tool should have a corresponding doc in docs/tools/<tool-name>.md
